      • getTopBotBit

        public static int getTopBotBit(int farAddress,
                               Series s)
        For Series 7 devices, it returns the top or bottom bit. For all other devices, it returns 0.
        Parameters:
        farAddress - The full 32-bit FAR address
        s - The devices series this FAR address targets
        Returns:
        If a Series 7 device, returns the top/bottom bit (bottom=1).
        Since:
        2020.2.1

      • getBlockAddress

                                  Series series)
        Gets the unique block address for the given FAR address. It essentially removes (zeros out) the minor field.
        Parameters:

        series - The series of the target device
        Returns:
        The block address of the FAR address.

      • getTopBot

        public static int getTopBot(Tile tile)
        Gets the top bottom bit for a particular tile by looking at the config row and SLR.
        Parameters:
        tile - The tile in the device of interest.
        Returns:
        0 if it is top (or all UltraScale/UltraScale+ devices) 1 if bottom.
        Since:
        2020.2.1

      • getFARConfigRowIndex

        public static int getFARConfigRowIndex(Tile tile)
        Gets the FAR row index based on the the tile's clock region.

        tile - The tile of interest
        Returns:
        The row index (accounting for top/bottom in Series 7) corresponding to the tile.
        Since:
        2020.2.1
